Class KuruczModelPanel

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
public class KuruczModelPanel
extends SpectrumPanel

This class provides a panel for including (or excluding) a Kurucz model spectrum in the target spectrum calculation and for setting all its properties. The Kurucz model spectrum is normalized to match a V magnitude.

propertiesPanel

public javax.swing.JPanel propertiesPanel(GenericSpectrum spectrum)
Returns the panel for setting the properties of the Kurucz model. The Kurucz model spectrum must be supplied. If the supplied spectrum happens to be no Kurucz model spectrum, the stack trace is output and an empty panel is returned.

Specified by:
propertiesPanel in class SpectrumPanel
Parameters:
spectrum - the spectrum (must be of the type KuruczModel)
Returns:
the panel for setting the properties of the given Kurucz model spectrum
